We recommended and Management agreed to:
 a. Submit the Certification by the LCE/Personnel Officer certifying that the activities/services cannot be provided by regular or permanent personnel of the agency as a supporting document to claim for compensation along with the duly accomplished Daily Time Record (DTR) and approved Accomplishment Report;
 b. Evaluate the need for the services of JO/COS and ensure that the hiring shall be resorted to based on the necessity and exigency of service, and refrain from hiring those whose functions are redundant to the functions of existing regular agency employees;
 c. Assess the current organizational structure and staffing to check for vacancies. In case of the availability of vacant positions, consider those qualified JO/COS personnel, especially those who have eligibilities, for appointment to the vacant regular plantilla positions in the agency. Employees who have been working for several years, especially those who perform essential services of a regular staff, may be hired as a casual employee charged under PS budget considering the ability to appropriate items without exceeding the prescribed PS limitation; and
 d. In case of the inadequacy of current plantilla positions, consider submitting a request to the DBM for the creation of new permanent positions that will perform regular functions and consider hiring the aforementioned personnel as regular permanent employees.

